<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Faintly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Faintly,</orth> 1) in a feeble, languid manner: <bibl n="shak. ven 482" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 482</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 740" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 740</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.281" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 281</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.282" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 282</bibl>.<lb />2) without zeal, not earnestly, not forcibly, slightly: <cit><quote>I f. broke with thee of Arthur's death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.227" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 227</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he prays but f. and would be denied,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 3, 103</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>'twas very f. he said Rise,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 1, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I have told you what I have seen, but f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 191</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>now he denies it f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 113</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>